<br>
max aa, no buffs or equip but counting QD3 aa.<br>
<br>
Conflagaration:<br>
622dmg<br>
7.2 time<br>
86.3dps<br>
<br>
Draught of Ro<br>
950dmg<br>
5.57 time<br>
165dps<br>
<br>
Strike of Solusek<br>
2740dmg<br>
9.45 time<br>
290dps<br>
<br>
I decided to point the bit of the conflagatation part out because it's a level 44 spell. You'll notice that as spells progress, their raw dps actually increases. Since the idea is to have spell power improve with level, I'll say that whatever improves for the spells consistently makes it better. Then compare Strike of Solusek and Draught of Ro: sos has more dps, which is really a better thing(more dps = better). There is a definite correlation between how fast the nukes pull aggro based on their damage, and I'd think that merely faster damage = faster aggro. When it comes to aggro limited situations, the faster nuke would allow you to use concussions to lower you aggro.<br>
<br>
Generally if I find i can do 5 draughts to a conc before starting to pull aggro on the same thing, I'll have about 1 1/2 concs per sos. With +35.5% dmg in the form of crits/focus I see(giving it 20%, though many suggest 18%):<br>
<br>
Draughts:<br>
6341dmg<br>
26 seconds<br>
244dps (or 296 if chain nuked)<br>
<br>
SOS:<br>
7425dmg<br>
22.6sec<br>
328.5dps<br>
<br>
^Keep in mind, though, that real dps often falls short of this due to lag, resists, and numerous other complications such as casting harvest. maelin legs aren't attributed to this. Silk legs hasn't dropped for us yet so I can't comment there (draughts have the added benefit of a lot of recast time). The point of all this is that with two basic nuke types, more dps is better even if unmanagable. this doesn't mean anyone should shun draughts- their resist check is very useful. I don't figure they'd make draughts not only less resistable, but do more dps than SOS. The key really is trying to see what works aggro wise and not shoeing yourself into one spell type, and ignoring the uses of the rest. I even have a really neat raid use for draught of thunder that involves getting summoned through walls to get unstuck if it happens. <br>
<br>
Aside from the resist check and the better recast time to damage ratio of the spell, I am curious what the preference is then. I think that isos/doi being better dps wise is something of a myth - check the big ice nuke thread and you can find a few more stats. Some have said that draughts are just lower aggro. It's logical then that the aggro of a nuke would most likely correlate to the damage. Strike of Solusek full hasted does its unmodified damage 82% times faster than a draught. That is almost twice as much. The aggro rate of this would then would need less compensation for your whole aggro to be closer to the main tank's, ie fewer concussions.<br>
<br>
I don't think it's more effective, but you might also say that it's more fun to chain nuke than to compensate with concussions. That is good- above all things you should enjoy playing your class. As for being more effective(not considering rains, which are also powerful), I don't see any evidence indicating that they are. DPS parses involve contingents, and most others are quire vague when they relate its superiority. When balancing the aggro vs a big nuke, I generally find that a pure usage of the big nuke is greater than the small one. another way I look at this is by taking a parse, counting the number of hits I landed in that amount of time and calculate the average spell damage. In one ep fight I did only 84,000dmg, when I did not crit and should have done over 100,000. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=filastilapplepie>Filastil Applepie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 167<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 6:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: small vs big</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Now, if you did not see the crit blast show up, one of two things happened. The first was that you turned off crits temporarily and thus didn't see it show up. The second and far more unlikely event was that you got a bugged crit, these things are one in maybe trillions and I do not know how they are reproduced. What will happen is that the crit won't show up at all, or show a different number than your regular hit.  <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
One of the things can be explained the crit with showing a diff num than your actual hit is when mob is Runed. The crit shows only the real HP recuction you did and the actual spelldamage the actual damage including the damage that went is rune the spell had.<br>
This can be easily seen in Sebilis where the Wizards rune themself. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79329">Filastil Applepie</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Arcanist<br>
Officer of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.lolf.de">Legion of Little Folk</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=veladorn>Veladorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<br>I have needs too!</span><br>  Posts: 1350<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 6:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: small vs big</span><hr size=1> Here are the reasons I use Draughts over SoS (I still do use SoS, just not as my main nuke)<br>
<br>
1. Better aggro control.  I'm sure its due to the reduced DPS but many of strats used on the encounters I've been facing of late require absolulty zero aggro being pulled away from the MT.  If the guild wipes, its not going to be because I turned the mob and pulled aggro.<br>
<br>
2.  Less summons - I like to use a horse for manaregen.  I know its annoying for the melees to suddenly have a big fat horse sitting on top of the mob where they are trying to hit it.  I used to justify getting summoned by saying, well the mob didn't hit me and its just part of the nuking strat doing max damage while staying alive.  Anymore though, Id just rather not get summoned if I can avoid it.<br>
<br>
3. Hit the mob more then once - I find on many of the mobs leading up to a boss mob on a raid, if I use SoS, I pretty much only get to nuke a mob once and its at times hard to time that one nuke.  Many times I have mis-timed it and ended up not hitting the mob at all.  Other times, do it too soon and summoned\dead.  With Draughts I can nuke a mob a few times and this holds my interest better. (talking about mobs leading up to a boss mob, not a named)<br>
<br>
4. Can nuke sooner - This ties in with #3 but I find it more fun to be able to nuke a mob early without retribution.<br>
<br>
5. Less resists\cost of resist - with draughts, the damage is more steady.  There is less of a chance the spell will be resisted and of one is resisted, the price to pay for that resist does not seem so great at that moment.  (loss of 3 seconds time vs 7 seconds with SoS).  Often, on mobs leading up to a boss mob, if SoS gets resisted, then I've done zero damage to that mob. At least if Draughts are resisted, I can still come back and hit the mob a couple more times doing at least some damage.<br>
<br>
I still do use SoS, I want to be clear about that.  Mostly I use it to finish off a mob though or on encounters where the MT says he has excellent aggro and to burn hard and fast. <p><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Valas Defai</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.insidiousblood.net/"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:x-small;">A member of Insidious Blood</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=211027&amp;resize=true" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-size:xx-small;">My Magelo</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=27078.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=27078.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=27078.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=27078.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=27078.topic><i